      },
      "date": "2011-06-16 20:56:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: (9 inline comments)\n\nI think the patch looks mostly pretty good now.\nI guess I need to see if I can incorporate the lsm passing through io struct to make it all even more consistent.\n\nthe liblustre still needs the mutex fix even if currently it's a noop.\n\nAnd I think the md->lsm in update_inode->replace_lsm is still not perfect with manual freeing there and such.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "693efba2eaa726b5fb129744dbad49e8a3dbec71",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-07-05 06:26:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: (33 inline comments)\n\nJC, sorry it took so long to look through your patch, but admittedly it is a very long patch...\n\nI think the major blockage at this point is the interoperability issue with clients that don't understand the new lmm_layout_gen field.  This has to be zeroed out on the MDS before returning the lmm to the client, or all older clients will break even when they don't need to.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "6a40ba361630d6217da1b50d33a354b43d297b34",
      "author": {
