          "date": "2011-12-03 01:00:33.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "subject": "LU-169 locking: implement layout lock for LOV EA",
        "message": "LU-169 locking: implement layout lock for LOV EA\n\nThis patch:\n- implements a new inode lock bit for layout lock\n- adds lsm refcounting\n- adds a generation number to the LOV EA\nEach time a lsm is used, a reference must be taken with\nll_lsm_get() or ll_lsm_get_io().\nA layout lock is acquired when taking a reference on a lsm.\nIf the lsm is needed for an io, the lock is hold up to the extent lock\nacquisition. If the lsm is not needed for io, the lock is given back\njust after reference is taken.\nWhen lsm is no more needed, if must be unreferenced with ll_lsm_put().\n\nChange-Id: I23b9bbfeeb6a59bbb21a2725bc2ee4d39ce14084\nSigned-off-by: Jacques-Charles Lafoucriere <jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr>\nSigned-off-by: Johann Lombardi <johann@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
